File: The ANC in the Eastern Cape has been calling for Andile Lungisa to step down since 2017. JOHANNESBURG - Andile Lungisa has resigned as ANC mayoral committee member in Nelson Mandela Bay. The ANC in the Eastern Cape has been calling for him to step down since 2017. READ: NMB councillors allegedly receive death threats In 2018, the Port Elizabeth Magistrate's Court sentenced Lungisa to three years in jail for assault. This comes after he hit DA councillor, Rano Kayser over the head with a glass jug during a council meeting in 2016. Lungisa is appealing his sentence.